The Churchill Show channel has reached a milestone of 0.5 billion views on YouTube. The channel, whose face is comedian Daniel ‘Churchill’ Ndambuki, is loved for the comical content and personality interviews that the comedian offers with 1.53 million subscribers. His Facebook page has a whopping 3.5 million followers. while his Instagram account has 2 million followers. Speaking to Word Is, Churchill said it is an important milestone. "It is something we really thank God for. That is going to inspire other content creators to put up their content. Because at the end of the day, what we are building is a community that together, we can change the society and make some crucial influence to make the world a better place." Churchill added that he is glad to be part of the community he has built.